    {
      "instruction": "<p>Melt 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> in a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span><strong> flour </strong>and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms – this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Gradually whisk 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>into the roux, a little at a time and cook for 4 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Add the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>cheese sauce</strong></p>",
